====Usage notes====
When the subject of the verb is the collective noun '''{{m|fr||ensemble}}''' followed by a predicate complement, the verb usually agrees with '''{{m|fr||ensemble}}'''. In this case, the focus lies on the collective whole referred to by '''{{m|fr||ensemble}}'''.
<br/>Though less common, it is not considered incorrect for the verb to agree with the grammatically plural predicate complement. In this case, the focus shifts to the individual elements of the collective whole. Plural agreement is more common with the indefinite article {{m|fr|un}} modifying '''{{m|fr||ensemble}}''' (i.e. '''{{m|fr||un ensemble}}''').<ref>[https://bdl.oqlf.gouv.qc.ca/bdl/gabarit_bdl.asp?id=4154 Banque de dépannage linguistique]</ref>

